ttitudes of the time. Accessibly written, with stories both heart-breaking and uplifting, the book is illustrated throughout with photographs.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aOral history. 0aRacially mixed childrenzGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aRacially mixed children. 0aSocial historyy20th century. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xBlacks. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xSocial aspectszGreat Britain. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh  aAmericans.  aBlack GIs.  aBritain.  aMixed-race.  aRacism.  aSecond World War.  aWhite women.  aWorld war II.  aillegitimacy.  ainterracial relationships.  a‘brown babies’.1 aBland, Lucy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152615405740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526154057423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526154057/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles